en_137005_0	President Maithreepala Sirisena announced that Dr. Indrajith Coomaraswamy will be appointed as the Governor of Central Bank on coming Monday, the 4th of July.
en_137005_1	Dr. Indrajith Coomaraswami who was born in 1950, pursued his education at Colombo Royal College and Harrow College in England is a prominent Sri Lankan economist who was the former Director Economic Affairs at the Commonwealth Secretariat from 1990 to 2008.
en_137005_2	In addition, Dr. Coomaraswami holds a first class honours degree from the Cambridge University and obtained his PhD from the Sussex University.
en_137005_3	After joining the Central Bank in the year 1973, he served as an officer attached to the sections of economic research, statistics and Bank Supervision until 1989.
en_137005_4	Dr. Indrajith Coomaraswami also served in the Ministry of Finance and Planning from 1981 to 1989.
